um standard for the masses to get educated.  I can't afford to send my kids to private school but if I could I'll be damned if I would want some idiot telling me where my children HAD to go even when I wanted and could afford something different for them.   Not only that, now Uncommon Core is the new standard bearer. Since it's enactment in my state last year I have a 2nd grader that has yet to receive anything other than a check mark.  Looking at &quot;spelling test&quot; words that are spelled wrong are marked as correct I assume because it was close enough.  Only left off the silent &quot;e&quot; in some cases.  I have to explain that even though it is marked right, it is actually not correct and I end up with an argument on my hands with a 7 year old because the teacher marked it as correct so it must be right.  I have to explain the real world doesn't allow &quot;close enough&quot; and there is in this instant only one right answer and what is written is not correct.   Thanks to all those bipartisan governor's for coming together and lowering the standard by the way.   Yes by all means force every single person, regardless of station in life to endure this. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1458" language="en" documentId="3942" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="bluelabel" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:10PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="35" thumbsDown="0" origId="3942" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1458"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>